<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="406" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,798,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="406">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,942,968]" pageId="1" pageNumber="406">Description.</emphasis>
Similar in appearance to other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ribaut" authorityYear="1952" box="[829,982,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsidius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[829,982,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="406">Macropsidius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[999,1109,942,969]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,188,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-36@2.[165,1423,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Macropsidius karatavicus sp. n. 1–2―male, dorsal view, 3―same, female, 4―male, face, 5―same, fe- male, 6–7―pygofer appendage, 8–10―penis, back view, 11–12―same, frontal and lateral view, 13–15―same, lateral view, 16–18―style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6838463" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6838463/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="406">Figs. 1–5</figureCitation>
). Pale yellowish brown with black spots on head, pro-, and mesonotum. Shape and location of spots typical for genus. Black pattern moderately developed, all spots separated from each other, specimens with partially merged spots absent in material studied. Forewings semitransparent, most veins of same color as membrane, veins of clavus and some other longitudinal veins sometimes milky white, especially, in basal parts. Anal margin, claval suture and, occasionally, apical margin and some cells darkened. Females usually lighter than males, with ovipositor sometimes extending beyond resting forewings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,798,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="406">
Pygofer appendages do not reach dorsal margin of pygofer, slightly S-shaped, sometimes, with sharply narrowed tip (
<figureCitation box="[271,378,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,188,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-36@2.[165,1423,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Macropsidius karatavicus sp. n. 1–2―male, dorsal view, 3―same, female, 4―male, face, 5―same, fe- male, 6–7―pygofer appendage, 8–10―penis, back view, 11–12―same, frontal and lateral view, 13–15―same, lateral view, 16–18―style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6838463" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6838463/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="406">Figs. 6–7</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft with very wide lateral carinae in basal half (
<figureCitation box="[1049,1170,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,188,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-36@2.[165,1423,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Macropsidius karatavicus sp. n. 1–2―male, dorsal view, 3―same, female, 4―male, face, 5―same, fe- male, 6–7―pygofer appendage, 8–10―penis, back view, 11–12―same, frontal and lateral view, 13–15―same, lateral view, 16–18―style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6838463" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6838463/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="406">Figs. 8–10</figureCitation>
), moderately developed ventral carina running along all shaft from base to gonopore (
<figureCitation box="[842,978,1266,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,188,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-36@2.[165,1423,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Macropsidius karatavicus sp. n. 1–2―male, dorsal view, 3―same, female, 4―male, face, 5―same, fe- male, 6–7―pygofer appendage, 8–10―penis, back view, 11–12―same, frontal and lateral view, 13–15―same, lateral view, 16–18―style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6838463" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6838463/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="406">Figs. 11–15</figureCitation>
), and with one or several small denticles on each side near apex. Ventral and lateral carinae perpendicular to each other (
<figureCitation box="[1031,1166,1303,1329]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,188,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-36@2.[165,1423,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Macropsidius karatavicus sp. n. 1–2―male, dorsal view, 3―same, female, 4―male, face, 5―same, fe- male, 6–7―pygofer appendage, 8–10―penis, back view, 11–12―same, frontal and lateral view, 13–15―same, lateral view, 16–18―style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6838463" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6838463/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="406">Figs. 11–12</figureCitation>
); for this reason, ventral carina hardly distinguishable in back view (
<figureCitation box="[652,774,1339,1365]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,188,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-36@2.[165,1423,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Macropsidius karatavicus sp. n. 1–2―male, dorsal view, 3―same, female, 4―male, face, 5―same, fe- male, 6–7―pygofer appendage, 8–10―penis, back view, 11–12―same, frontal and lateral view, 13–15―same, lateral view, 16–18―style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6838463" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6838463/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="406">Figs. 8–10</figureCitation>
) and, 
<emphasis box="[847,962,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="406">vice versa</emphasis>
, lateral carinae almost invisible in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[221,358,1374,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,188,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-36@2.[165,1423,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Macropsidius karatavicus sp. n. 1–2―male, dorsal view, 3―same, female, 4―male, face, 5―same, fe- male, 6–7―pygofer appendage, 8–10―penis, back view, 11–12―same, frontal and lateral view, 13–15―same, lateral view, 16–18―style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6838463" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6838463/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="406">Figs. 13–15</figureCitation>
). Styles with lobe-like rounded or somewhat angular tips (
<figureCitation box="[1013,1150,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,188,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-36@2.[165,1423,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Macropsidius karatavicus sp. n. 1–2―male, dorsal view, 3―same, female, 4―male, face, 5―same, fe- male, 6–7―pygofer appendage, 8–10―penis, back view, 11–12―same, frontal and lateral view, 13–15―same, lateral view, 16–18―style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6838463" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6838463/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="406">Figs. 16–18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,798,2013]" box="[199,713,1411,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="406">
Body length: 
<specimenCount box="[352,375,1411,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="406" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
